What:		/sys/class/fpga_card/cardX/dfl_reload/name
Date:		Nov 2022
KernelVersion:  6.1
Contact:	Tianfei Zhang <tianfei.zhang@intel.com>
Description:	Read-only. This file returns the name of the reload device.

What:		/sys/class/fpga_card/cardX/dfl_reload/available_images
Date:		Nov 2022
KernelVersion:  6.1
Contact:	Tianfei Zhang <tianfei.zhang@intel.com>
Description:	Read-only. This file returns a space separated list of
		key words that may be written into the image_load file
		described below. These keywords decribe an FPGA, BMC,
		or firmware image in FLASH or EEPROM storage that may
		be loaded.

What:		/sys/class/fpga_card/cardX/dfl_reload/image_reload
Date:		Nov 2022
KernelVersion:  6.1
Contact:	Tianfei Zhang <tianfei.zhang@intel.com>
Description:	Write-only. A key word may be written to this file to
		trigger a reload of an FPGA, BMC, or firmware image from
		FLASH or EEPROM. Refer to the available_images file for a
		list of supported key words for the underlying device.
		Writing an unsupported string to this file will result in
		EINVAL being returned.

What:		/sys/class/fpga_card/cardX/dfl_reload/reload_wait_secs
Date:		Nov 2022
KernelVersion:  6.1
Contact:	Tianfei Zhang <tianfei.zhang@intel.com>
Description:	Read-Write. Image reload timeout in seconds. Read this file
		to get the current timeout for image realod. Write this file
		to set a new timeout for image reload.
